TY  - JOUR
T1  - A Linear Programming Solution to Dynamic Leontief type Models
AU  - Wagner, Harvey M.
Y1  - 1957/04/01
PY  - 1957
DA  - 1957/04/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.3.3.234
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.3.3.234
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 234
EP  - 254
VL  - 3
IS  - 3
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - Much research has been undertaken in the past several years on the uses of Leontief input-output matrices; applications have been made ranging from industrial growth models to models of interregional dynamics to estimates of structural changes in the economy. This paper discusses a general linear programming formulation of Leontief type relationships. Since we may construct models for a single firm analogous to Leontief macro-economic systems, our results are applicable to a wide variety of situations.
